                     <interp inst="t18030420-7-person109" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn - I am a pawnbroker, in Cable-street, (produces a watch, outside case gold, and inside case silver gilt); I took it in of the prisoner on the 25th of November; it has a chain, two gold seals, and two gold lockets attached to it.</p>

               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18030420-7-person110">
                  THOMAS 
                  GRIFFITHS
               <interp inst="t18030420-7-person110" type="surname" value="GRIFFITHS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18030420-7-person110" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18030420-7-person110" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn. - I am an officer: On the 24th of March, about half past one, I was sent for to the Black Horse in Nightingale-lane, where I found the prisoner sitting with the prosecutor in a box in the tap-room; I took the prisoner backwards into a club-room, and asked him what he had done with the property he had taken from that person; he said, he had pledged them, and had the duplicates about him; he unbuttoned the waistband of his breeches, took out a pin, and pulled out these duplicates. - (Produces them)(The various articles were identified by Mr. and Mrs. Sanders.)</p>
               <p>The prisoner left his defence to his Counsel, and called two witnesses, who gave him a good character.</p>
               <p>GUILTY, aged 28,</p>
               <p>Of <rs id="t18030420-7-verdict35" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18030420-7-verdict35" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18030420-7-verdict35" type="verdictSubcategory" value="lesserOffence"></interp>
               stealing, but not in the dwelling-house
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18030420-7-punish36" type="punishmentDescription">
